==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Styptic
<hw>Styp"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stypticus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to contract.]</ety>
<def>Producing contraction; stopping bleeding; having the quality of
restraining hemorrhage when applied to the bleeding part;
astringent.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>stiptic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Styptic weed</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an American
leguminous herb (<spn>Cassia occidentalis</spn>) closely related to the
wild senna.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Styptic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Styptic
<hw>Styp"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A styptic
medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Styptical</ent>⟦br⟧
